$interpreted: Tica: Isn't that Pang?!
Pang: What are you doing here? Didn't you have to bring a package back to the Academy?
Tica: Hehehe~ I'm so awesome that the headmaster sent me on a new mission!
Pang: This Headmaster...must be as dumb as a doornail.
Tica: What about you, Pang? Still looking for your partner?
Pang: Perhaps he's wandered into Whistlewood Valley, alas... no sightings yet.
Leah: Lost in Whistlewood Valley? Maybe he's been attacked by the giant flower!
Pang: Giant flower?
Fatima: Whistlewood Valley is under threat by an enormous flower. It's very dangerous. We're on our way to finish it off.
Pang: Hmm, do you need help?
Leah: Of course, the more the merrier! Tiger, bro, please come with us~
Fatima: The giant flower is up ahead, pick up the pace.
Tica: Not there yet? I can bascially predict the attack patterns of these plants!
Fatima: Hush, you'll startle the...
Pang: CAREFUL!
Pang: HEY! Tica, you alright?!
Tica: I'm, I'm fine! EEEEK~
Pang: KEEP YOUR EYES ON THE PRIZE! We'll assist from this side.
Tica: GOT IT!
Puggi: Ooh, my...is it day yet? Can I eat breakfast now?
Puggi: Holy moly~Pang! Haven't seen you so long and wow wee get any fatter!? You're already over the hill! Keep growing sideways and you'll be a whale!
Puggi: The ground's gonna rumble under those fat paws; you'll start earthquakes and tsunamis, I'm telling you, stop eating so much...
Pang: Shut...up. What are you carrying on your back?
Puggi: The treasures I found in this fat flower~
Puggi: Hehehe, not sharing my goodies with you buttheads!
Tica: So...this chattering ball of fluff is your partner?
Puggi: Woo, a pretty one over here! What color do you like? I think white is nice, pure and innocent just like rabbit girl's hair...
Puggi: Pang what the hell!? Can't an bird pick up chicks around here?
Pang: Blabbermouth. Been searching for eons to find you, maybe I should throw you in a pot and make some dinner!
Puggi: Don't pay attention to Pang; he's just a jaded tiger from the east!
Puggi: Goodies~ Are only to be shared with good girls~
Leah: Could that be?
Tica: Seems like it. That's the seed Headmaster Ceres is looking for!
Fatima: Hmph. Now that you've got it, vacate our land immediately. I'm going back to the tribe to report that the flower has fallen.
Pang: My journey awaits, take care.
Puggi: Don't miss me too much. See you soon!
Leah: Mission accomplished! Don't forget your promise, sister~
Tica: Eh? Wait, wait a moment!
